HEADWORD: Trecento
<hw>Tre*cen"to</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. & a.</pos> <ety>[It.,
three hundred, abbr. for thirteen hundred.]</ety> <def>The fourteenth
century, when applied to Italian art, literature, etc. It marks the
period of Dante, Petrarch, and boccaccio in literature, and of Giotto in
painting.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

